SIMPLE: crowfoot
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Crowfoot
<hw>Crow"foot`</hw> <pr>(kr?"f??t`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The genus <gen>Ranunculus</gen>, of many species;
some are common weeds, others are flowering plants of considerable
beauty.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A number of small cords rove
through a long block, or euphroe, to suspend an awning by.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Mil.)</fld> <def>A caltrop.</def> <altsp>[Written
also <asp>crow's-foot</asp>.]</altsp> ⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Well Boring)</fld> <def>A tool with a side claw for
recovering broken rods, etc.</def> <rj><au>Raymond.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Crowkeeper</ent>⟦br⟧
